    <item>
      <title>Fastest Way to Create Money Making Videos – Part 2</title>
      <link>http://www.videoboss2011.com/63/create-money-making-videos-2/</link>
      <comments>http://www.videoboss2011.com/63/create-money-making-videos-2/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Wed, 08 Jun 2011 07:54:12 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Video Boss</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Video Boss]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.videoboss2011.com/?p=63</guid>
      <description>By now you should have your VIDEO SCRIPT and VIDEO OPENER ready to roll. So the next logical step is to frame your video. Step-3: Frame Your Video You take the video script and chop it into frames, so you know what exactly is going to go into each frame of the video. And again [...]&lt;p&gt;A post from: &lt;a href="http://www.videoboss2011.com"&gt;Video Boss Bonus | Video Boss Review&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/video-boss-bonus-video-boss-review/Video_Boss_Bonus_-_Video_Boss_Review-Fastest_Way_to_Create_Money_Making_Videos__Part_2.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>By now you should have your VIDEO SCRIPT and VIDEO OPENER ready to roll. So the next logical step is to frame your video.</p>
<p><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Step-3: Frame Your Video</span></em></p>
<p>You take the video script and chop it into frames, so you know what exactly is going to go into each frame of the video. And again remember the FAB video scripting technique. Each frame will talk about ONE feature and its associated advantages and benefits. You should be able come up with some 5-10 frames based on the individual features of the product.</p>
<p>Now all you have to do is simply open up PowerPoint or Keynote (if using MAC) and load each slide with the content you have developed for each frame. But before you do that go search for a good PowerPoint template related to the product you are promoting. This will make you video look more engaging. Ok so you have got all the frames loaded in PowerPoint, what next?</p>
<p><em><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Step-4: Adding Sizzle to your video</span></em></p>
<p>A picture is worth a thousand words. You want your video to look engaging and not monotonous and boring. Now there are two types of images that you can add to your video. One is the images that showcase the features of the product and you will most likely get this from the product manufacturers if you are promoting an affiliate offer.</p>
<p>The second kind of images that you need to add to your video is called “EMOTIONAL ACCELERATORS”. These are images that bring out powerful emotion that written words can’t express. And there are hundreds of websites where you can find these types of images that come with no royalty fee. Clipart.com is one such site where you can grab a lot of these images for cheap.</p>
<p>One last thing you want to do is add some PowerPoint transitions between the frames. Like when you move from one slide to another you can apply a flipping effect (like flipping each page on a book), a sliding effect, or a spinning effect and so on. It’s very easy to do this in just 2 or 3 clicks using the PowerPoint animations features. So take advantage of this feature that comes free with PowerPoint.</p>
<p>The reason why we want to do this is because every time something flies in or moves it resets the viewers’ attention. So in essence it gets the reader to watch the full video and more video viewership.</p>
<p>Now that we have everything ready, how do we put it all together to produce our money making video? And that’s the final and most important step coming up next.</p>
<p>A post from: <a href="http://www.videoboss2011.com">Video Boss Bonus | Video Boss Review</a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
