    <item>
      <title>Bad Video Makes More Money Than NO Video – Proof Inside</title>
      <link>http://www.videoboss2011.com/54/video-makes-more-money/</link>
      <comments>http://www.videoboss2011.com/54/video-makes-more-money/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Thu, 02 Jun 2011 20:20:48 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Video Boss</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Video Boss]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.videoboss2011.com/?p=54</guid>
      <description>How much money can you make with online video? How about $5,000,000? Yes you heard me right, that much was made from 3 product launches that used video instead of a 30 page sales letter. And the guy behind making the videos &amp;#8211; Andy Jenkins is giving away some of the secrets of producing such [...]&lt;p&gt;A post from: &lt;a href="http://www.videoboss2011.com"&gt;Video Boss Bonus | Video Boss Review&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/video-boss-bonus-video-boss-review/Video_Boss_Bonus_-_Video_Boss_Review-Bad_Video_Makes_More_Money_Than_NO_Video__Proof_Inside.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>How much money can you make with online video? How about $5,000,000?</p>
<p>Yes you heard me right, that much was made from 3 product launches that used video instead of a 30 page sales letter. And the guy behind making the videos &#8211; Andy Jenkins is giving away some of the secrets of producing such money making videos.</p>
<p>If you thought producing such videos require expensive video equipment, video editing software, slick copywriting and geeky skills to put it all together then you are in for a real surprise. Because these videos were made using Microsoft PowerPoint. You can use something simple as a Flip-cam and produce videos that are TV-Studio quality.</p>
<p>Now if producing video is that easy why isn’t everybody making such videos?</p>
<p>The thing is not many people know that’s it quite easy to produce the videos. Head over to YouTube and you will find tons of amateur videos. However when you want to do videos for your business, you do want to look professional and interesting to the people watching your videos. And that is what makes most people to shy away from making videos.</p>
<p>In fact Andy Jenkins himself is a camera shy person that he used a cartoon character and did a voice over for the video.<br />
And of the hundreds of videos he’s produced he shows up in front of the camera in less than 5 videos. So even if you are camera shy you can still make videos that make money.</p>
<p>And here is the kicker. Guess what?</p>
<p>Amateur videos on YouTube and other popular video hosting sites are getting ranked on first page of Google results pretty fast. If people who have no idea about marketing can make a casual video and make it to the first page of Google, you can do much better with all the marketing knowledge you have. Your video could hit the first page of Google within a weeks’ time, while a traditional website might take a few months of SEO to get onto the first page.</p>
<p>And you can compete with authority sites that have been ranking on the first page for ages.</p>
<p>Tell me if you find anything better than this – creating a 5 minute video, hitting the first of Google in less than a week and converting all that traffic into cold hard cash. Video has been gaining momentum over the last couple of years and it’s on the rise. Now is the time to ride the wave and profit.</p>
<p>Click here to watch the video</p>
<p>A post from: <a href="http://www.videoboss2011.com">Video Boss Bonus | Video Boss Review</a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
